Package: weechat-headless
Source: weechat (2.1-2)
Version: 2.1-2+b1
Architecture: amd64
Maintainer: Emmanuel Bouthenot <kolter@debian.org>
Installed-Size: 1045
Depends: libc6 (>= 2.16), libcurl3-gnutls (>= 7.16.2), libgcrypt20 (>= 1.8.0), libgnutls30 (>= 3.5.6), weechat-core (= 2.1-2+b1)
Recommends: weechat-plugins (= 2.1-2+b1)
Suggests: weechat-doc (= 2.1-2)
Section: net
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://weechat.org/
Description: Fast, light and extensible chat client - headless client
 WeeChat (Wee Enhanced Environment for Chat) is a fast and light chat client
 for many operating systems. Everything can be done with a keyboard.
 It is customizable and extensible with plugins/scripts, and includes:
  - support of IRC protocol (native)
  - support of XMPP/Jabber protocol (with additional script)
  - nicklist
  - smart hotlist
  - horizontal and vertical split
  - double charset support (decode/encode)
  - FIFO pipe for remote control
  - 256 colors support
  - incremental text search
  - dynamic filtering of buffer content
  - Perl, Python, Ruby, Lua, Tcl, Scheme and PHP scripting
  - script manager
  - spell checking
  - highly customizable and extensible
  - and much more!
 .
 This package provides the headless client.
